                    "value": "<p>Vineyard must be productive of much good in the <add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        our sacred faith.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Hoping that the Al<del>l</del>mighty may prolong\n                                        your life,<lb/> and bestow upon you his choicest blessings;\n                                        that you may be<lb/> able for many years to come, as you\n                                        have done hitherto,<lb/> to labor zealously and effect much\n                                        good in the cause of<lb/> our holy Religion. I subscribe\n                                        myself</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">Your very obt. Servt.</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Henry Mack</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>\n                                        <date>June 8<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1852</date>. </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><hi rend=\"underline\">Note</hi>: We insert\n                                        cheerfully <persName>Mr Mack's</persName> letter which gives\n                                                  <add>?</add><lb/> an account of the\n                                                  people<add>?</add> of the congregation to which he\n                                        is attached; but we would<lb/> call his attention to the\n                                        last statement at the bottom of page 47 of this column<lb/>\n                                        which will prove to him that we had not forgotten the\n                                        existence of the school<lb/> of which he speaks with such\n                                        hopeful terms, and in which we trust he may<lb/> not be\n    