                  listen to our <add>?</add> based and heart in the\n                                        glorious<lb/> work? Why should slight misapprehension\n                                                  <add>?</add> hearts <add>?</add> should<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add>? We know well enough that emotional jealousies\n                                        arising<lb/> from a difference of our birth place, early\n                                        habits &amp; early <add>?</add> are<lb/> great drawbacks to\n                                        a thorough union of Israelites; but in the name of<lb/> our\n                                        common religion, let us cease to call each other “bigots” or\n                                        “new light”<lb/> or other terms of reproach which likeliness\n                                        of mind is so ready to reveal.<lb/> We have at last all but\n                                        one <add>?</add> “the promotion of the good cause; at\n                                        all<lb/> events we all employ this magical phrase; let us\n                                        then show that we<lb/> are in earnest, and our enemies will\n                                        be unfounded when they see the Jews<lb/> united for\n                                                  <placeName>Israel's</placeName> God and\n                                                  <placeName>Israel's</placeName> Law, and\n                                                  <placeName>Israel's</placeName>\n                                        <add>?</add>! Come brothers!<lb/> meet as friends who have\n                                        been estranged and have again been united<lb/> in peace in\n                                        God's cause for God's sake; you are all to affect much<lb/>\n                                        good by union; but you are powerless if